<topic template="Default" lasteditedby="rbwinst-pr" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation="../helpproject.xsd">
  <title translate="true">Drawing the Grid</title>
  <body>
    <header>
      <para styleclass="Heading2_atoc_"><text styleclass="Heading1" translate="true">Drawing the Grid</text></para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Normal" style="text-align:left; text-indent:48px; margin-top:0px; margin-right:0px; margin-bottom:10px; margin-left:0px; line-height:1.0; white-space:normal; page-break-inside:auto; page-break-after:auto; tabstops:none;"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">If the user selects </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Grid|Add Vertical Grid Line </text><image src="InsertVerticalGridLine.png" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Normal"><title translate="true">Add Vertical Grid Line button</title></image><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> or </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Grid|Add Horizontal Grid Line </text><image src="InsertHorizontalGridLine.png" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Normal"><title translate="true">Grid|Add Horizontal Grid Line button</title></image><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> and then clicks on the top, front, or side view of the model, a horizontal or vertical grid line will be drawn at the mouse position.  Layer boundaries can be drawn this way in PHAST models, but with MODFLOW models, the </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MODFLOW_Layer_Groups_Dialog_Box" styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">MODFLOW Layer Groups</link><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> dialog box must be used to define the layers. &#160;The grid can be rotated around its center by selecting </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Grid|Drag to Rotate </text><image src="RotateGrid.png" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Normal"><title translate="true">Drag to Rotate button</title></image><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> and then dragging with the mouse on the top view of the model. Other menu items that are useful in drawing the grid include </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Grid|Delete Grid Line</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">&#32;</text><image src="DeleteGridLineA.png" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Normal"><title translate="true">Delete Grid Line button</title></image><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">, </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Grid|Move Grid Line</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">&#32;</text><image src="MoveGridLineA.png" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Normal"><title translate="true">Move Grid Line button</title></image><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">, </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Grid|Subdivide Grid Elements</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">&#32;</text><image src="SubdivideElements.png" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Normal"><title translate="true">Subdivide Grid Elements button</title></image><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">, </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Grid|Set Width</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">&#32;</text><image src="SetElementWidth.png" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Normal"><title translate="true">Set Width button</title></image><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">, and </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Grid|Smooth Grid...</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">  See &quot;</text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="Editing_the_Grid" styleclass="Normal" translate="true">Editing the Grid</link><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">&quot;</text><conditional-text type="IF" value="PRINT,PDF,EBOOK"/><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> in the help system</text><conditional-text type="END"/><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> for more information on these menu items. </text><conditional-text type="IF" value="FOOTPRINT"/><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">Note: drawing &#160;the grid is not allowed with </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="Footprint_Properties_Dialog_Bo" styleclass="Normal" translate="true">Well Footprints</link><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">. Instead, </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="Using_Objects_to_Specify_the_G" styleclass="Normal" translate="true">use objects to specify the grid</link><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">.</text><conditional-text type="END"/></para>
  </body>
</topic>
